Too often compulsion effects are a lazy substitute for good writing. It's nice to be reminded that they can be employed very well indeed in the hands of a skilled author. Very creepy existential horror delivered via excessive hugs.

I also want to applaud your journal entries here: I thought the pacing was excellent, telling the story evocatively and succinctly without feeling rushed or forced-marched. Very organic feel to it. You nearly had me in real tears with his line about not being able to escape by shooting upthat's some heartbreaking shit right there. Heartily upvoted!

